arcade.agent.cell

Class CARTCell

  • java.lang.Object
    • arcade.agent.cell.CARTCell
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cell, java.io.Serializable, sim.engine.Steppable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CART4Cell, CART8Cell

    public abstract class CARTCell
extends java.lang.Object
implements Cell
    Implementation of Cell for generic CAR T-cell.

    CARTCell agents exist in one of thirteen states: neutral, apoptotic, migratory, proliferative, senescent, cytotoxic (CD8), stimulatory (CD4), exhausted, anergic, starved, or paused. The neutral state is an transition state for "undecided" cells, and does not have any biological analog.

    CARTCell agents have two required Module types: metabolism and inflammation. Metabolism controls changes in cell energy and volume. Inflammation controls effector functions.

    General order of rules for the TissueCell step:

    • update age
    • check lifespan (possible change to apoptotic)
    • step metabolism module
    • check energy status (possible change to starved, apoptotic)
    • step inflammation module
    • check if neutral or paused (change to proliferative, migratory, senescent, cytotoxic, stimulatory, exhasuted, anergic)

    Cell parameters are tracked using a map between the parameter name and a Parameter object. Daughter cell parameter values are drawn from a distribution centered on the parent cell parameter with the specified amount of heterogeneity.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CARTCell

        public CARTCell(int pop,
                Location loc,
                double vol,
                int age,
                java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Parameter> p)
        Creates a CARTCell agent.

        CARTCell agents are by default assigned as type = neutral. Any extending constructors should specify type and/or code as needed.

        Cell parameters are drawn from Parameter distributions. A new map of Parameter objects is created using these values as the new means of the distributions. This cell parameter map is used when constructing daughter cell agents, so any daughter cells will draw their parameter values from the parent distribution (rather than the default distribution). Note that META_PREF, META_PREF_IL2, META_PREF_ACTIVE. GLUC_UPTAKE_RATE, GLUC_UPTAKE_RATE_IL2, and GLUC_UPTAKE_RATE_ACTIVE are assigned to the cell parameter map, but are updated separately by the Module constructors. Note that parameters involved in calculating receptor binding affinity, such as CAR_AFFINITY, CAR_ALPHA, CAR_BETA, SELF_AFFINITY, SELF_ALPHA, SELF_BETA, CONTACT_FRAC are assigned values but those values are the same in all daughter cells as these are biophsyical properties unaffected by heterogenity except in the case of receptor mutation which is not accoutned for in this model.

        Parameters:
        pop - the population index
        loc - the location of the cell
        vol - the initial (and critical) volume of the cell
        age - the initial age of the cell in minutes
        p - the map of parameter name to Parameter objects

      • bindTarget

        public Cell bindTarget(sim.engine.SimState state,
                       Location loc)
        Determines if CAR T cell agent is bound to neighbor through receptor-target binding.

        Searches the number of allowed neighbors in series, calculates bound probability to antigen and self receptors, compares values to random variable. Sets flags accordingly and returns a target cell if one was bound by antigen or self receptor.

        Parameters:
        state - the MASON simulation state
        loc - the location of the CAR T-cell
        Returns:
        target cell if bound one, null otherwise
